The central government has been closely following the development of the situation in Hong Kong, a spokesperson said. Yang Guang, spokesperson for the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council, made the remarks on the recent protests and violent incidents in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, at a press conference held in Beijing on Monday. 
